{
  "texts": [
    "Such a family is sometimes called a cover of A.",
    "The notion of cover is classical in the algebraic topology literature (e.g.",
    "[7] chapter 3, section I, example 6 and [3] chapter 5, section 3).A p-site a ≡ ( (I, A, α)) ≡ ( (I, A, (A i))) can also be characterized by its parting map Π I,A α denoted π a.",
    "One has A i = {x ∈ A|π a (x) ∋ i}, π a (a) = {j ∈ I|A j ∋ a}.",
    "We denote by PSITE(I, A) the set of all p-sites that depend on (I, A)."
  ]
}